      <persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Namık</forename><surname>Görgüç</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.7d5d8ec5">Görgüç, Namık</ref></persName><persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Selahattin </forename><surname>Giz</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.dce0efc3">Giz, Selahattin </ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A man in elegant urban clothes stands ostentatiously in front of a fashion shop in an alley in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=M2">Mahmutpaşa çarşısı</ref>, his elbow casually resting on a showcase and looking towards the camera. A customer to his left is inspecting a sweater. She is wearing a headscarf and an overcoat. The walls of the shop are covered with shirts, hats and sweaters. Inside, two more men are standing in the dark.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The photograph belongs to a series taken for an article in Cumhuriyet with the title, ‘Preparations for bayram in the city’.</ab>
